summary: An internal email chain forwarding voicemails from an unidentified woman in Australia who claims to be a prisoner and references crimes against her, mentioning Lisa Marie Presley, the British Royal Family, President Trump, and Jeffrey Epstein. The agency is blocking the number and not taking further action due to the foreign jurisdiction.

events.title: Voicemails from Australian caller
events.description: An unidentified woman in Australia leaves three voicemails claiming to be a prisoner, referencing crimes committed against her, and naming Lisa Marie Presley, the British Royal Family, President Trump, and Jeffrey Epstein.

keyFacts: An unidentified woman from Australia left three voicemails on August 10, 2020, claiming to be a prisoner and referencing crimes committed against her.
The caller mentioned Lisa Marie Presley, the British Royal Family, President Trump, and Jeffrey Epstein in her messages.
The receiving agency decided to block the caller's number and take no further action due to the foreign jurisdiction and principles of international comity.
The document shows a pattern of unsolicited tips or claims being forwarded internally but not actively pursued if they originate from overseas.
The British Royal Family is referenced as a collective entity, but no specific royal family members are named.
